Master Blog Hero Image Prompt

Create a premium, calming hero image for a blog aimed at therapists and counsellors.

The style should feel minimal, thoughtful and sophisticated rather than corporate or overly polished.

Use soft natural light, muted earthy colours, gentle contrast and plenty of negative space. The image should evoke calm, clarity, reflection and trust.

Avoid obvious therapy clichés such as two people talking on a sofa, hands cupped together, puzzle pieces, light bulbs, stock-business imagery, or people pointing at laptops.

Instead, create a subtle conceptual photograph that represents the core idea of the article through everyday objects, architecture, landscapes or carefully composed scenes.

The composition should feel editorial, similar to a high-end magazine feature.

Leave generous empty space so a title could comfortably sit over the image.

Use a wide 16:9 aspect ratio suitable for a website hero image.

The image should feel authentic, timeless and quietly confident.

It should align with the Alexander Watson brand values:

Clarity before complexity
Calm over noise
Thoughtful rather than sales-driven
Human rather than corporate
Premium without feeling expensive
Minimal, understated and warm

Do not include text, logos, watermarks or typography.

This article is about:

[Replace this section with a one or two sentence summary of the specific blog post.]

Create an image that communicates this idea metaphorically rather than literally.